      open launch

}
```

I turned it into: (psuedocode)

```
function prelaunch{
   create mouse listener
   open launch
}

function launch{
   if logs is true then open logs, else open no logs version
      open launch
}
```

The flickering issue happens because a new mouse listener is called which flips the boolean and relaunches the app. In my first iteration of the code, this cause a loop of new mouse listeners being created WHILE im pressing the button.

